<Layout title="Evidencias | Juan Pablo Moreno">
	<section class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
		<!-- Header -->
		<div class="text-center mb-12">
			<h1 class="text-4xl font-extrabold mb-2">
				<span class="bg-gradient-to-r from-primary to-secondary bg-clip-text text-transparent">
					Evidencias
				</span>
			</h1>
			<p class="text-lg opacity-70 mt-4">Portafolio de evidencias — Bases de Datos 2</p>
			<div class="w-24 h-1 bg-gradient-to-r from-primary to-secondary mx-auto rounded-full mt-4"></div>
		</div>

		<!-- Categories Grid -->
		<div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
			
			<!-- SQL -->
			<div class="card md:col-span-2 bg-base-200 shadow-xl hover:shadow-2xl transition-all duration-300 border border-base-300">
				<div class="card-body p-8">
					<div class="flex items-center gap-4 mb-6">
						<div class="w-16 h-16 rounded-2xl bg-primary/10 flex items-center justify-center">
							<svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="1.5" stroke="currentColor" class="w-8 h-8 text-primary">
								<path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M20.25 6.375c0 2.278-3.694 4.125-8.25 4.125S3.75 8.653 3.75 6.375m16.5 0c0-2.278-3.694-4.125-8.25-4.125S3.75 4.097 3.75 6.375m16.5 0v11.25c0 2.278-3.694 4.125-8.25 4.125s-8.25-1.847-8.25-4.125V6.375m16.5 0v3.75m-16.5-3.75v3.75m16.5 0v3.75C20.25 16.153 16.556 18 12 18s-8.25-1.847-8.25-4.125v-3.75m16.5 0c0 2.278-3.694 4.125-8.25 4.125s-8.25-1.847-8.25-4.125" />
							</svg>
						</div>
						<h2 class="card-title text-3xl font-bold">SQL</h2>
					</div>

					<div class="space-y-8">
						<!-- Ejemplo 1 -->
						<div class="bg-base-100 rounded-xl p-6 border border-base-300">
							<h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 flex items-center gap-2">
								<span class="badge badge-primary">1</span> Empleados con múltiples cargos
							</h3>
							<p class="text-base opacity-80 mb-4">
								Para este caso, necesitaba saber qué empleados han hecho carrera interna, pasando por diferentes puestos. La consulta cuenta su historial de cargos y me filtra solo a los que han tenido más de un rol en la compañía.
							</p>
							<div class="mockup-code bg-[#1a1b26] text-white overflow-x-auto">
								<pre class="px-5 py-4"><code>SELECT   
    e.EMPLOYEE_ID AS ID,  
    e.FIRST_NAME || ' ' || e.LAST_NAME AS NOMBRE_COMPLETO,  
    COUNT(hc.JOB_ID) AS NUMERO_CARGOS  
FROM hr.EMPLOYEES e  
LEFT JOIN hr.JOB_HISTORY hc   
    ON e.EMPLOYEE_ID = hc.EMPLOYEE_ID  
GROUP BY e.EMPLOYEE_ID, e.FIRST_NAME, e.LAST_NAME  
HAVING COUNT(hc.JOB_ID) > 1 
ORDER BY e.EMPLOYEE_ID;</code></pre>
							</div>
						</div>

						<!-- Ejemplo 2 -->
						<div class="bg-base-100 rounded-xl p-6 border border-base-300">
							<h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 flex items-center gap-2">
								<span class="badge badge-primary">2</span> Salarios en Europa
							</h3>
							<p class="text-base opacity-80 mb-4">
								Aquí el objetivo era filtrar al personal de Europa con un salario específico (entre 4 y 6 mil). Tuve que conectar varias tablas desde Empleados hasta Regiones para poder filtrar por ubicación geográfica y rango de sueldo simultáneamente.
							</p>
							<div class="mockup-code bg-[#1a1b26] text-white overflow-x-auto">
								<pre class="px-5 py-4"><code>SELECT 
    CONCAT(E.FIRST_NAME, ' ', E.LAST_NAME) AS NAME, 
    C.COUNTRY_NAME AS COUNTRY, 
    E.SALARY
FROM HR.EMPLOYEES E 
JOIN HR.DEPARTMENTS D ON E.DEPARTMENT_ID = D.DEPARTMENT_ID
JOIN HR.LOCATIONS L ON L.LOCATION_ID = D.LOCATION_ID
JOIN HR.COUNTRIES C ON L.COUNTRY_ID = C.COUNTRY_ID
JOIN HR.REGIONS R ON C.REGION_ID = R.REGION_ID
WHERE R.REGION_ID = 10 
AND E.SALARY BETWEEN 4000 AND 6000;</code></pre>
							</div>
						</div>

						<!-- Ejemplo 3 -->
						<div class="bg-base-100 rounded-xl p-6 border border-base-300">
							<h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 flex items-center gap-2">
								<span class="badge badge-primary">3</span> Jerarquía y Enmascaramiento
							</h3>
							<p class="text-base opacity-80 mb-4">
								Esta consulta ayuda a visualizar la cadena de mando, mostrando empleado y jefe lado a lado. De paso, practiqué manipulación de strings ocultando parcialmente los correos para que solo se vean las primeras letras.
							</p>
							<div class="mockup-code bg-[#1a1b26] text-white overflow-x-auto">
								<pre class="px-5 py-4"><code>SELECT
    E.FIRST_NAME || ' ' || E.LAST_NAME AS EMPLEADO,
    LPAD(SUBSTR(E.EMAIL, 1, 3), 9, '*') AS EMAIL_EMPLEADO,
 
    M.FIRST_NAME || ' ' || M.LAST_NAME AS JEFE,
    LPAD(SUBSTR(M.EMAIL, 1, 3), 9, '*') AS EMAIL_JEFE
 
FROM HR.EMPLOYEES E
LEFT JOIN HR.EMPLOYEES M ON E.MANAGER_ID = M.EMPLOYEE_ID
ORDER BY E.LAST_NAME;</code></pre>
							</div>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>

			<!-- PL/SQL Scripts -->
			<div class="card bg-base-200 shadow-xl hover:shadow-2xl transition-all duration-300 hover:-translate-y-1 border border-base-300">
				<div class="card-body items-center text-center p-8">
					<div class="w-16 h-16 rounded-2xl bg-secondary/10 flex items-center justify-center mb-4">
						<svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="1.5" stroke="currentColor" class="w-8 h-8 text-secondary">
							<path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M17.25 6.75 22.5 12l-5.25 5.25m-10.5 0L1.5 12l5.25-5.25m7.5-3-4.5 16.5" />
						</svg>
					</div>
					<h2 class="card-title text-2xl font-bold">PL/SQL Scripts</h2>
					<div class="divider my-2"></div>
					<div class="flex flex-col items-center gap-3 py-4">
						<div class="badge badge-outline badge-lg gap-2">
							<svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2" stroke="currentColor" class="w-4 h-4">
								<path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M12 6v6h4.5m4.5 0a9 9 0 1 1-18 0 9 9 0 0 1 18 0Z" />
							</svg>
							Próximamente
						</div>
						<p class="text-sm opacity-60">Procedimientos, funciones y triggers</p>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>

			<!-- NoSQL -->
			<div class="card bg-base-200 shadow-xl hover:shadow-2xl transition-all duration-300 hover:-translate-y-1 border border-base-300">
				<div class="card-body items-center text-center p-8">
					<div class="w-16 h-16 rounded-2xl bg-accent/10 flex items-center justify-center mb-4">
						<svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="1.5" stroke="currentColor" class="w-8 h-8 text-accent">
							<path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M3.75 9.776c.112-.017.227-.026.344-.026h15.812c.117 0 .232.009.344.026m-16.5 0a2.25 2.25 0 0 0-1.883 2.542l.857 6a2.25 2.25 0 0 0 2.227 1.932H19.05a2.25 2.25 0 0 0 2.227-1.932l.857-6a2.25 2.25 0 0 0-1.883-2.542m-16.5 0V6A2.25 2.25 0 0 1 6 3.75h3.879a1.5 1.5 0 0 1 1.06.44l2.122 2.12a1.5 1.5 0 0 0 1.06.44H18A2.25 2.25 0 0 1 20.25 9v.776" />
						</svg>
					</div>
					<h2 class="card-title text-2xl font-bold">NoSQL</h2>
					<div class="divider my-2"></div>
					<div class="flex flex-col items-center gap-3 py-4">
						<div class="badge badge-outline badge-lg gap-2">
							<svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2" stroke="currentColor" class="w-4 h-4">
								<path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M12 6v6h4.5m4.5 0a9 9 0 1 1-18 0 9 9 0 0 1 18 0Z" />
							</svg>
							Próximamente
						</div>
						<p class="text-sm opacity-60">MongoDB, Redis y bases documentales</p>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>

			<!-- Proyecto -->
			<div class="card bg-base-200 shadow-xl hover:shadow-2xl transition-all duration-300 hover:-translate-y-1 border border-base-300">
				<div class="card-body items-center text-center p-8">
					<div class="w-16 h-16 rounded-2xl bg-warning/10 flex items-center justify-center mb-4">
						<svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="1.5" stroke="currentColor" class="w-8 h-8 text-warning">
